jenkins CD/CD setup

If you have only **2 EC2 instances**:

* EC2-1 → Jenkins Master
* EC2-2 → Jenkins Agent

Then follow this setup from scratch.

# Architecture

```text
GitHub
   |
   v
Jenkins Master (EC2-1)
   |
SSH Connection
   |
   v
Jenkins Agent (EC2-2)
   |
Docker Build
   |
Amazon ECR
```

---

# Step 1: Create ECR Repository

Login to AWS CLI from Jenkins Agent:

```bash
aws configure
```

Provide:

```text
AWS Access Key
AWS Secret Key
Region = ap-south-1
```

Create repository:

```bash
aws ecr create-repository \
--repository-name myapp \
--region ap-south-1
```

Verify:

```bash
aws ecr describe-repositories
```

---

# Step 2: Install Jenkins on Master EC2

Amazon Linux:

```bash
sudo yum update -y
```

Install Java:

```bash
sudo dnf install java-17-amazon-corretto -y
```

Add Jenkins repo:

```bash
sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo \
https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
```

```bash
sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key
```

Install Jenkins:

```bash
sudo yum install jenkins -y
```

Start Jenkins:

```bash
sudo systemctl enable jenkins
sudo systemctl start jenkins
```

Open Security Group:

```text
8080
```

Get password:

```bash
sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
```

Access:

```text
http://MASTER_PUBLIC_IP:8080
```

---

# Step 3: Install Docker on Agent

On EC2-2:

```bash
sudo yum install docker -y
```

```bash
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker
```

Verify:

```bash
docker --version
```

