# Step 4: Install AWS CLI on Agent

```bash
sudo yum install unzip -y
```

```bash
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o awscliv2.zip
```

```bash
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install
```

Verify:

```bash
aws --version
```

---

# Step 5: Create Jenkins User on Agent

```bash
sudo useradd jenkins
```

Set password:

```bash
sudo passwd jenkins
```

Add docker permission:

```bash
sudo usermod -aG docker jenkins
```

---

# Step 6: Configure SSH Between Master and Agent

On Jenkins Master:

```bash
sudo su - jenkins
```

Generate key:

```bash
ssh-keygen
```

Press Enter.

Copy key:

```bash
ssh-copy-id jenkins@AGENT_PRIVATE_IP
```

Test:

```bash
ssh jenkins@AGENT_PRIVATE_IP
```

Should login without password.

---

# Step 7: Configure Agent in Jenkins

Install plugin:

```text
Manage Jenkins
→ Plugins
→ SSH Build Agents
```

Create Node:

```text
Manage Jenkins
→ Nodes
→ New Node
```

Example:

```text
Name: agent1
Label: docker-agent
Remote Root Directory:
/home/jenkins
```

Launch Method:

```text
Launch agents via SSH
```

Provide:

```text
Private IP of Agent
SSH Credential
```

Save.

Agent should become:

```text
Online
```

