# Step 10: IAM Permissions (Recommended)

Instead of storing AWS keys:

1. Create IAM Role.
2. Attach ECR permissions.
3. Attach role to Agent EC2.

Required permissions:

```text
AmazonEC2ContainerRegistryFullAccess
```

Then no `aws configure` is needed.

---

## Interview Flow

> Developer pushes code to GitHub. Jenkins Master receives the trigger and schedules the build on Jenkins Agent. The Agent checks out the code, builds the Docker image, authenticates to Amazon ECR using IAM Role, tags the image, and pushes it to ECR. Jenkins Master only manages the pipeline, while all build activities run on the Agent node.
